\subtree{
\title{Etymology as Decomposition}
\pre{\startverb
| Morpheme | Meaning | Trit |
|----------|---------|------|
| tri- | three | ±0 (balanced) |
| -mester | measure | ±0 (neutral) |
| bi- | two | unbalanced |
| se- (six) | two×three | balanced via factorization |
\stopverb}

\p{\strong{Trimester} resonates with GF(3) because "tri-" encodes triadic structure in the morpheme itself.}
}

